writeObject

protected void writeObject(ParameterCache_mxJPO _paramCache,
                           Appendable _out)
                    throws IOException
Writes specific information about the cached channel to the given writer instance. This includes
  • hidden flag (only if hidden)
  • label
  • href
  • alt
  • height
  • settings defined as properties starting with "%" in AbstractAdminObject_mxJPO.getPropertiesMap()
  • command references orderCmds

Specified by:
writeObject in class AbstractAdminObject_mxJPO
Parameters:
_paramCache - parameter cache
_out - appendable instance to the TCL update file
Throws:
IOException - if the TCL update code for the channel could not be written

update

protected void update(ParameterCache_mxJPO _paramCache,
                      CharSequence _preMQLCode,
                      CharSequence _postMQLCode,
                      CharSequence _preTCLCode,
                      Map<String,String> _tclVariables,
                      File _sourceFile)
               throws Exception
The method overwrites the original method to append the MQL statements in the _preMQLCode to reset this channel. Following steps are done:
  • reset HRef, description, alt and label
  • set height to 0
  • remove all settings and commands

Overrides:
update in class AbstractAdminObject_mxJPO
Parameters:
_paramCache - parameter cache
_preMQLCode - MQL statements which must be called before the TCL code is executed
_postMQLCode - MQL statements which must be called after the TCL code is executed
_preTCLCode - TCL code which is defined before the source file is sourced
_tclVariables - map of all TCL variables where the key is the name and the value is value of the TCL variable (the value is automatically converted to TCL syntax!)
_sourceFile - souce file with the TCL code to update
Throws:
Exception - if the update from derived class failed
